<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,726,1941]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1879,1905]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet of the new species is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1072,1125,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">apex</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1180,1295,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">triangulus</emphasis>
, referring to the shape of the apical process of the gnathos.
</paragraph>
